000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">mammals</text><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"202.09714181082592\" y=\"143.55555555555557\" height=\"152.44444444444443\" width=\"40.72571454729353\" fill=\"#B3B3B3\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><text xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"0\" y=\"0\" text-anchor=\"end\" transform=\"translate(232.37999908447267 315.84) rotate(-40)\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">birds</text><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"283.548570905413\" y=\"174.66666666666666\" height=\"121.33333333333334\" width=\"40.72571454729353\" fill=\"#B3B3B3\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><text xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"0\" y=\"0\" text-anchor=\"end\" transform=\"translate(313.8314281790598 315.84) rotate(-40)\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">insects</text><text text-anchor=\"middle\" transform=\"translate(222.45999908447266 24)\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">Percent of Drawings</text><text text-anchor=\"middle\" transform=\"translate(222.45999908447266 48)\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">Containing an Example of</text><text text-anchor=\"middle\" transform=\"translate(222.45999908447266 72)\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">Each Animal Group</text><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" fill=\"none\" x=\"171.9609603881836\" y=\"414.2607421875\" height=\"26.84\" width=\"100.99807739257812\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><rect xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" x=\"178.9609603881836\" y=\"421.2607421875\" height=\"12\" width=\"12\" fill=\"#B3B3B3\" stroke=\"#000000\" stroke-linejoin=\"mitre\" stroke-width=\"0.9\"/><text transform=\"translate(197.9609603881836 433.2607421875)\" text-anchor=\"top\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">Animal</text></g></svg></figure><div class=\"sr-only\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Long description for bar graph titled Percent of Drawings Containing an Example of Each Animal Group\"><ul>\n<li>The Percent of drawings data for the 3 bars are as follows:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>mammals: 80.5&nbsp;</li>\n<li>birds: 68.6</li>\n<li>insects: 54.6</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div>\n<p>Researchers Kate Howlett and Edgar Turner asked 401 schoolchildren in the United Kingdom to draw and label local wildlife. The researchers suggest that the children may be more aware of mammals than of other animals in their environments.</p>",
