7421875)\" text-anchor=\"top\" fill=\"#000000\" font-size=\"19.84\" font-family=\"Crimson Text\">Animal</text></g></svg></figure><div class=\"sr-only\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Long description for bar graph titled Percent of Drawings Containing an Example of Each Animal Group\"><ul>\n<li>The Percent of drawings data for the 3 bars are as follows:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>mammals: 80.5&nbsp;</li>\n<li>birds: 68.6</li>\n<li>insects: 54.6</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div>\n<p>Researchers Kate Howlett and Edgar Turner asked 401 schoolchildren in the United Kingdom to draw and label local wildlife. The researchers suggest that the children may be more aware of mammals than of other animals in their environments.</p>"
